<h1 id="title">Lata Mangeshkar</h1>
<p id="para">The Nightingale of India</p>
<figure id="img-div">
  <img id="image" src="https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQAEKINgIcsrWGt5IWu2AiyAKRiE_yGgvlnrOQLtWYV-cjPSy4lhptVxWThx_cqUUAgzJFhlYZgWVoxTKhVUiQVZQ" alt="pic">
  <figcaption id="img-caption">
Lata Mangeshkar, an iconic Indian playback singer lovingly called Swar Kokila (vocal nightingale).
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
  <div id="tribute-info">
    <h2>Here's a time line of Lata Mangeshkar's life:</h2>
    <div id="list">
    <ul>
      <li><b>1929</b> - September 28, Indore, India</li>
      <li><b>1934</b> - "Started acting in her father's musical plays at age five"</li>
      <li><b>1942</b> - Recorded her first playback song for a Marathi film, Kiti Hasaal, at age 13 "</li>
      <li><b>1946</b> - Recorded her first Hindi film playback song for Aap Ki Seva Mein</li>
      <li><b>1948</b> - Received her first major break with the song "Dil Mera Toda" in the movie Majboor </li>
      <li><b>1949</b> - Became the go-to voice of the heroine</li>
      <li><b>1969</b>-received Padma Bhushan </li>
            <li><b>1995</b>- Her songs in DDLJ movie reached a record breaking performance.Recorded songs for the soundtracks of more than 2,000 Indian films </li>

      <li><b>2022</b>-Died in Mumbai on February 6, 2022 at the age of 92 </li>
      </div>
    </div>
<blockquote>"Music expresses that which cannot be said and on which it is impossible to be silent."
 - Victor Hugo </blockquote>
